This depends on the chip, unfortunately. Most of the time, modifing a state 
is just the change of a bit. Of course, most of the time this will result in 
the chip registers  to be re-evaluated. Both the Permedia and the Voodoo 
drivers have host-memory backups of the resister, and registers will only be 
transfered to the chip when they've changed, to minimize bus traffic. 
Frequent state changes will of course result in larger amount of bus traffic.

> > Additive blending is achieved by W3D_ONE, W3D_ONE.
>
>     BTW. Is substractive blending possible?

No. The blend function is always SrcColor * SrcFactor + DstColor * DstFactor. 
You can't change the operation. I think some chips can do subtraction, but 
it's not in Warp3D yet. If we get enough chips that support it, it will make 
it's way into Warp3D....

