> can't get Warp3d to work on it. I can't even get the warptest demo
> or the gears demo to work, let alone Shogo or HereticII.
> All I get is a gray screen or window, and then the system hangs.

First of all, remember that there's no 68k version. WarpTest is 68k, so it 
will not dinf any driver.

If you've got the version from the CD, you probably got the one-library 
version (look for a Warp3D/hwdrivers/W3D_Avenger_PPC.library). This one's a 
very old one, and it's got problems on screens with big endian byte ordering 
(i.e. screens of format 16 BIT), and requires modes with 16 BIT PC. The newer 
version that can be downloaded form Matay's web site is a two-library version 
(W3D_AvengerBE_PPC.library and W3D_AvengerLE_PPC.library). This one's 
independant of the byte ordering.

I suggest that you download the newer version from the Matay web site, 
uninstall Warp3D, and reinstall it (to be sure you don't have old libraries 
around)...

> Amiga 3000/040 tower

I never tested it on an A3000, although I can't think of a reason that it 
will not work...

